14 safety, and was named Legislator of the Year by the Georgia Chapter of the American
15 Academy of Pediatrics for her strong advocacy on behalf of Georgia's children; and
16 WHEREAS, Dr. Au's significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable patience
17 and diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of this state
18 have earned her the respect and admiration of her colleagues, associates, and constituents;
19 and
20 WHEREAS, Dr. Au, doing what she would do for any of her patients, answered a very late
21 call from Representative Teddy Reese regarding his mother and a very severe medical
22 situation; and
23 WHEREAS, thanks to the leadership, care, compassion, and direction of Dr. Au, Mrs. Carrie
24 Prosser, mother of Representative Teddy Reese, immediately received the appropriate
25 medical attention which the family is convinced saved the life of Mrs. Prosser; and
26 WHEREAS, she is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
27 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
28 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
29 dedicated legislator and medical professional be appropriately recognized.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
31 the members of this body recognize, commend, and congratulate Dr. Michelle Au for her
32 efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated public service to the State of Georgia and extend
33 the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
